choices.text: There were no doctors or medical equipment available there. The nurses there did their best to help my mom and me with whatever little they had. The nurses gave me a small toy to keep me calm and they also gave my mom some medicines to ease her labor pain. I was born after 24 hours of labor pain and the doctors said that I was too weak to survive. But my mom did not give up and kept me close to her heart. She breastfed me and took good care of me. She did not let me cry or feel hungry. I was a preemie baby and I had to stay in the NICU for a month. My mom used to visit me every day and talk to me. She would sing me lullabies and tell me stories. She would also bring me toys and clothes. I slowly started gaining weight and my health improved. I was discharged from the hospital after a month. My mom was happy to see me back home and she thanked the doctors and nurses for taking good care of me. I am now six years old and I am in first grade.
